snippet: All three incumbents who ran won their races in Coralville, Iowa, on Tuesday, despite being targeted by the conservative group Americans for Prosperity over the town’s debt.
abstract: Mayoral and City Council candidates in Coralville, Iowa, who were closely aligned with deep-pocketed conservative political group Americans for Prosperity, are roundly defeated in a sharp rebuke of outside influence in local politics; all three incumbents who ran won their races, despite being targeted by conservative-backed opponents.
lead_paragraph: All three incumbents who ran won their races in Coralville, Iowa, on Tuesday, despite being targeted by the conservative group Americans for Prosperity over the town’s debt.

headline.main: Iowa Town’s Vote Delivers Rebuke to Kochs’ Group
